  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is legally defined as conducting financial transactions to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Key legal elements typically include:\n\n1. Specific intent to disguise the source of funds\n2. Knowing the money comes from criminal activity\n3. Transforming illegal proceeds into seemingly legitimate funds\n\nGeneral legal components include:\n- Placement (introducing illegal money into financial system)\n- Layering (concealing the source through complex transactions)\n- Integration (making funds appear legitimate)\n\nSpecific definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most countries criminalize these core activities.",
